    <td><a href="forum.php?id=0000000170"><b>Re: Epic! Epic! Epic!</b></a>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="2" class="lvl2">

  <tr>

    <td>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="2" class="lvl3">

  <tr>

    <td>2003-05-31 19:12:16 by <a href="profile.php?id=0000000020">Magijedi</a> | viewed 81 times
    </td>

  </tr></table>Allow me to throw my 2CP in here, Ladies, and Gentlemen...<br><br><br>I am still discussing this with Gaunja, but this is my point by point plan on making the guild succeed, and please put your trust in my words because I amseeing this in action on another server even as I type this. <br><br>To Start off...Those of you who are Pre-55s need to start grouping in Plane of Justice.<br>There is NO Better exp than Planes of Power. It's as simple as that.<br>Once you guys are 55ish, a BUNCH of doors will open. Let me ellaborate on the battle plan during thenext few months.<br><br>A: The Halo of Chaos tag and the Chaos and Destruction Tag are, for the most part, Tarnished on Tallon Zek. It's not by fault of one or many, but an unfortunate side-effect of the fierce rivalry on our server.<br>Therefore: A new guildtag will be voted upon in the next few weeks.<br><br>B: Leadership will go through some changes, with Officers being assigned special duties, so that not all officers recruit, and not all officers are to plan raids. <br><br>C: An Application proccess will come into effect, so that we can root out the good from the bad. Although many of you loyal guildies apped and got accepted and are still here, there are many people who will just join and leave for no reason, and we want to maket his a QUALITY guild, not just for us, but for all of you.<br><br>D: Active grouping: Guys, As a Magician, let me tell you no one appreciates Soloing more than I.<br>However,<br>Exp in PoP is so good that it's better to group than to NOT group. We will begin to organize lots of groups, so that we take over PoJ pretty much until we are all at least lvl 55 or so.<br><br>Now, those were the plans for the guild to grow. <br>Here are the plans for the guild to RAID :-p<br><br>A: Start off Raiding in Umbral Plains. It's a great spot to get to know what Raid encounters are like. It will give everyone a prime opportunity to start to get to know their class's role in a raid and also get some decent loot.<br><br><br>B: Start Raiding Kael. Akui's post was what really made me post this whole thing. Kael may seem dumb, but you have to look at the long run.<br>With Kael, comes good CoV Faction. With Good CoV faction, after a month or two, we could start doing HoT, and THEN we are going to be KNEE DEEP in LOOT.<br>We have to start off small and progress. That's how all the other guilds did, even Pande. And that's how we will work it out. Kael may not be the funnest of places, but you get the faction needed, and you get the experience(Not EXP, but just in general, knowledge) of indoor raiding. Plus some decent quest items drop once in a while.<br><br>C: Once we have an active force that is raid-capable of at least 24 people, we can start doing SOME Epic mobs like Venril Sathir, and Planar raids like the new Hate (its fun) and the rest of the pre-PoP zones.<br>By about this point, we should all be in the 55-60ish range<br>If we get this far, we'll be about on Par with SotG.<br><br>D: Once we have enough time spent doing all these things, and once we get an active roster of about 30 people for raids, we can start doing that which I mentioned a lil while ago, which is HoT(Halls of Testing) Dragons, giant creatures, ok exp, GREAT loot.<br>After a month or two of doing HoT, ( and collecting some Sleeper Tomb Keys ), we should have a raid force of about 35-40, and we can start inching our way into Sleeper's tomb.<br><br>E: After we get a raid force of about 60 active members lvls 55+, we can start actually doing Sleepers Tomb. <br>And let me explain something, with Sleepers Tomb, we will be very very very powerful. It's not just any guild that can make it in there. But if you guys take it seriously, stick to the guild, and follow this plan, this guild will be doing ST by about November. <br><br>Now, I know this seems far away, but what else are you going to do? Level up to 61, Bend over, and let Pande/Disc/Indig stick it in you and make you their bitch?<br>Guys we can do it without them. We can be a big guild and still not have to rely on the help or alliances of these other guys.<br>If we get HoT ready, Epics will be a breeze. Just stick to it.<br><br>More will be posted as decisions are made. 
    </td>

