    <td><a href="forum.php?id=0000000136"><b>Re: Being an officer</b></a>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="2" class="lvl2">

  <tr>

    <td>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="2" class="lvl3">

  <tr>

    <td>2003-05-24 18:33:41 by <a href="profile.php?id=0000000020">Magijedi</a> | viewed 89 times
    </td>

  </tr></table>Acutally, That wasn't Ammberr.<br>That was Me.<br>Magijedi, you know.<br>The Guildleader :-p<br><br>As far as officership, my friends, I haven't been on Tallon a lot, and those of you who I do know well enough to make officers already are, with the possible exception of Banrak(I can't remember if Gaunja promoted him or not).<br><br>I don't doubt that many of you have sterling qualities that make you each very valuable members of the guild.<br>However, right now is not the time to worry about promotion. Truth be told, Officership isn't a promotion, it's an enforced responsibility.<br>Officers are nothing more than people that have to answer for a lot of people, and that's how Leaders are as well, except we make the final calls on things.<br><br>At one point, I had thought that the way to make the guild work was to swell it with membership and get everyone to show up.<br>That's not how it works :-)<br>The most important thing right now isn't recruiting members, it's leveling up and getting to know your class.<br>If I get back on Tallon on July 11th, and I find at LEAST 18 ACTIVE members who are at LEAST 49+ (if you're not, it's ok, but 49+ is what we're aiming for), then we could TOTALLY be a guild to be reckonned with. <br>All everyone has to do is get it into your minds that this guild isn't going to work without the special attention of each and everyone of you. You all have to be reliable to show up/notify us if you can't on raids. You all have to be reliable not to fight with one another.<br>You all have to be reliable enough to say to yourselves "OK, I may not get as good exp by grouping with soandso, but it will help the guild in the long run" <br>Get to KNOW each other.<br>After I get back, and after Gaunja Levels up his cleric (The idiot turned down an offer to have a 52 cleric for free), we will make a decision.<br><br>Either this guild moves forward, or this guild dissapears and we give up. <br>I have spent 9 months working on 2 different guilds with all my time and effort. I don't feel like giving up. I don't think, I KNOW we can make it if we could just get the levels and participation we need.<br>ONE DAY in Kael arena and we'll be a WAY better guild than we are now.<br>JUST ONE DAY<br>All I ask of you all is that when I get back I can expect ONE DAY a week from you all to show up. <br>And when the guild starts moving again as it should be, with me and Gaunja back in full swing, THEN some more officers will be appointed.<br><br><br>All this stupid rant boils down to is this:<br>If you want to be an officer, understand the responsibilities that come with it, accept them, and start showing that you're capable BEFORE you get the promotion.<br>Get some gruops going in PoJ/PoD/Kael...work on CoV faction in Kael, level up in PoJ, do some group sin Seb...<br>If I get back and I see someone took the initiative and started getting the guild working, they will be an Officer, and they will be of the highest standing in the guild.<br><br>Goodluck to you all while I'm on leave to Stormhammer.
    </td>

