    <td><a href="forum.php?id=0000000064"><b>Updated Guild Protocols and Procedures</b></a>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="2" class="lvl2">

  <tr>

    <td>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="2" class="lvl3">

  <tr>

    <td>2003-05-10 22:01:35 by <a href="profile.php?id=0000000020">Magijedi</a> | viewed 113 times
    </td>

  </tr></table>Disclaimer:<br>These rules can change at any moment and I am authorized to put them into full effect as of any changes.<br>They are to be kept sacred, and followed word for word.<br><br>These rules are going to be Categorized. If you are looking for the different categories, they will be CAPPED for ease of browsing. <br><br>PUBLIC RELATIONS:<br><br>Remember, you are all representatives of the guild as a whole. Act mature in all the things you do. Don't Gloat at people, don't talk smack to people. If you PK, that's fine. Just don't gloat like a bloke.<br><br>NO ONE is an official representative of the guild on inter-guild relations, except for Gaunja and Myself. Any questions/comments related to alliances/pacts/lack thereof, should be noted, and <a href="forum.php?new=leadership">posted on the LEADERS board</a> for revew by me and Gaunja. Officers will, of course, do their job of answering for our guildies and answering general questions about the guild and telling people about our guild, but as far as detailistic discussions between powers, that belongs soley to the leadership. <br><br><br>PLAYER KILLING (PKing):<br><br>Chaos and Destruction currently are non-alligned.<br>We have no allies, and no one likes us very much. I don't wanna say we are KOS to anyone, because that all boils down to your personal views on the matter. You don't HAVE to kill someone who isn't in Chaos, but then again, it's always best to get the jump on someone before they get the jump on you.<br><br>Rules regarding Chaos:<br><br>PK anyone you want. Just don't be too unfair to people by overwhelming them in numbers.<br><br>Avoid EXP Killing. We may be Chaos, but we aren't bastards. If you feel it neccessary, do it. But avoid it at all costs. <br><br>CCing is ok IF they have been bastards.<br>Bind Camping is Illegal as per EQ rules. Any Bind Camping is not sponsored by the guild.<br><br>**************Fighting Other Guild Members:<br>There is to be NO In Fighting. Not even if you're joking. The only way, and I mean the ONLY way, is if you both decide to duel and /d each other.<br><br><br>RECRUITING:<br>Do NOT Recruit anyone of 39th or lower lvl. <br>I would rather say 46 or lower, but then again, it's too early to make that restriction on all classes.<br>Therefore:<br>Clerics, Enchanters, and Warriors of lvl 39+ are welcome to Join.<br>All other classes must be 46+ from now on. <br><br>Very soon, an application process will come into full effect. So try not to let just anyone join.<br>Make sure the person you're inviting is ready for the responsibility of showing up for raids or at the very least notifying us if they CANNOT show up. Make sure they are willing to help the guild and interact with us. <br><br><br>ATTENDANCE and RAIDING:<br>Attendance is MANDATORY for ALL Raids UNLESS you post on the LEADERSHIP board at the VERY LEAST 3 days before a planned raid. <br>First Breach of this rule will be a verbal warning.<br>Second Breach will result in Demotion and/or temporary loss of looting privelages.<br>Third Breach will result in expulsion from guild and permanent KOS status. <br><br>Don't take this offensively, but There is NO Excuse for NOT informing us that you can't make it on a pre-scheduled raid. <br><br><br>INTERNAL ISSUES:<br><br>For any Internal Scuffles:<br><br>1. All problems within the guild shall be brought the the attention of an officer.<br>2. All problems within the guild involving Officers as well shall be brought to the Leadership.<br><br>Leadership(to my knowledge) currently consists of:<br><a href="profile.php?id=18">Gaunja</a><br><a href="profile.php?id=20">Magijedi</a><br><br>Officers are there to administrate for, and aid, the leadership.<br><br>3. ALL problems within the guild, no matter who it involves, is to be kept in TELLS.<br>If any of you have a problem with one another, you can either send Officers/Leadership a tell, OR post it on the Leadership board. <br><br>The <a href="forum.php?board=leadership">Leadership board</a> is a private board that can only be viewed by me and Gaunja and we can view any personal/private problems you may have. <br><br>I will NOT allow any fighting in guild chat. That's not what it's there for. That's not what the GUILD is there for. <br>I will issue a warning on the first incident.<br>Any further incidents I see will result in a vote by Leadership on suspension.<br>In all cases submitted for Review to Leadership, a Judgement SHALL be made and Penalties will incur. So think clearly before making a big deal out of something small. <br> <br>LOOTING:<br>We will be Raiding much more in the next few months, and this is an important issue.<br>If you want to Loot, You have to attend. <br>We aren't using a Raid Point system, per say...<br>Looting will be decided on the fly by me or Gaunja. During unofficial raids/groups, looting will go to the roll.<br>Key rules for Unofficial raids: NEED B4 GREED.<br>If you have a Crystalline robe and another has an oracle robe(Old school comparrison I know) and an advisor robe drops, give the one with the oracle robe the advisor robe. That kinda thing.<br><br>If you want to get the loots and you want to get the epic pieces and you want to get the quest drops and you want to get the plat drops, SHOW UP FOR MORE RAIDS. Me and Jon are going to keep tabs on participation and interaction within the guild and that is how it will be decided. <br><br>Don't worry, those of you who remember how it was in Halo of Chaos when I was the leader, they can attest to the fact that I am 100% Fair in my loot decisions and assign it as needed/deserved. <br>Everything will be spread equally. <br>By this time next month, some of us COULD(Keyword) be walking around with +10 or more to all stat items. COULD COULD COULD!!!<br>IT ALL DEPENDS ON YOU!!!!<br>AHHHHAHAHAHAHAHA <br>Ok end of Rules Section.<br>Thanks all. <br>May Chaos Reign Supreme. 
    </td>

